category: 11-LETTER WORDS
category comment: 

clue: Let's horse around on this far straightaway on an oval racecourse; it might also be a way to limber up your lumbar region

response: the backstretch

clue: Keep up! The son of your brother's child is this relationship to you, old-timer

response: great nephew (grandnephew)

clue: A college football player normally gets 5 years of it, & can compete in 4 seasons

response: eligibility

clue: Flammable, but with 2 more letters, & if you even think of saying inflammable, I'm coming over there

response: combustible

clue: It's--sob!--an 11-letter word for weeping, or the secretion of tears

response: lacrimation

